 from plumpe oasys dt navy mil david plumpe subject re pink noise reply to plumpe oasys dt navy mil david plumpe organization carderock division nswc bethesda md lines one eight in sci electronics wayne uva three eight six schools virginia edu tony wayne writes what is pink noise and how is it used in sound experiments pink noise has constant power per geometric frequency increment octave one three octave etc thus the one zero khz two zero khz octave has the same amount of noise power as the one zero hz two zero hz octave white noise has constant power per arithmetic frequency increment hz khz etc thus the one zero khz one zero one khz band has the same amount of noise power as the one zero hz one one zero hz band both bands are one zero zero hz wide pink noise can be made by passing white noise thru a three db octave filter usually approximated by a network of several rc pairs note you can t get three db octave by using half a six db octave network pink noise is commonly used in audio power response measurements it shows up on audio spectrum analyzers with octave related bands as a flat line across the bands davep